TATTRUSR.DESC: This is a system generated number which will uniquely identify each exception message. It is made up of the SPECIFICATION_ID with 3,4, or 5 randomly generated digits concatenated on the right.

TATTRUSR.NAME: MESSAGE_NAME_TX
TATTRUSR.DESC:
Full Name: Exception Message Name
Description: This is the name of the Exception Message and is used during the maintenance of Exception Messages as a mechanism to locate particular exception conditions or exception message text.

TATTRUSR.NAME: MESSAGE_TX
TATTRUSR.DESC:
Full Name: Exception Message Text
Description: This string returns the message (via other component exception messaging services) to the application for use. It is also used internal to the component if the application has requested that the component display a message. Note, if the message is to be used by Composer as an exit state message, it can only support 80 characters of data.

TATTRUSR.NAME: ATTRIBUTE_ID
TATTRUSR.DESC: This is a system generated number which will uniquely identify each attribute. It is made up of the SPECIFICATION_ID with 3,4, or 5 randomly generated digits concatenated on the right.

TATTRUSR.NAME: ATTRIBUTE_NAME_TX
TATTRUSR.DESC:
Full Name: Attribute Name
Description: This attribute is used to define an attribute value for Hilight fields on a transaction screen. This field will indicate the name of the field to highlight on the screen. The field name will typically be the same name as the public field name found in the public data of a component called from the transaction.

TATTRUSR.NAME: CONTEXT_STRING_TX
TATTRUSR.DESC:
Full Name: Exception Context String
Description: This string can be returned by a component and used to contain additional information about the context of the exception. It is not a message explaining the exception, but instead can contain data that could be put into a formatted message by one of the exception message services. It should use a forward slash (\) character to separate data. This standard allows the message services to determine what data is available. If parameter based messages are to be used, it is the responsibility of the component raising the exception to format a valid Context_String, even if its only placing empty forward slashes. If a forward slash is required in the context data string, surround the string segment in double quotations to isolate the string.

TATTRUSR.NAME: SEVERITY_CD
TATTRUSR.DESC:
Full Name: Exception Severity Code
Description: A flag indicating the severity of the exception. Current values would be I- Information, W-Warning and E-Error. The Severity Code is used in conjunction with the exception message to determine how to format the message for a system user. For instance in Block Mode, the Severity Code would be used to dtermine the colour of the message returned on a screen. In GUI, the severity code would indicate which Icon should be associated with the message in a message box. The severity code is not to be used for program logic. Program logic should be on the exception which is indicated by the return code.

TATTRUSR.NAME: ACTIVITY_CD
TATTRUSR.DESC:
Full Name: Exception Activity Code
Description: A code value allowing services to accept in, or return out an action indicator. This would be similar to the COMMAND value maintained by Composer, and would usually be used in a Case structure to perform multiple actions. It also can be used to return some context information about an exception that was being raised.

TATTRUSR.NAME: CHECKSUM_TX
TATTRUSR.DESC:
Full Name: Exception Checksum
Description: This string represents a 32 bit checksum, calculated on a data block. It is used to ensure that data over or under runs have not occurred. It is expected that a set of external action blocks, provided by Castek, can be used to calculate a checksum.

TATTRUSR.NAME: ROLLBACK_INDICATOR_TX
TATTRUSR.DESC: Description: A flag requesting that the operation invoker rollback changes made to persistent storage.

TATTRUSR.NAME: RGV_ACTION_TX

TATTRUSR.NAME: RGV_SCROLL_UP_FG

TATTRUSR.NAME: RGV_SCROLL_DOWN_FG

TATTRUSR.NAME: SEVERITY_CODE
TATTRUSR.DESC:
Full Name: Exception Severity Code
Description: A flag indicating the severity of the exception. Current values would be I- Information, W-Warning and E-Error. The Severity Code is used in conjunction with the exception message to determine how to format the message for a system user. For instance in Block Mode, the Severity Code would be used to dtermine the colour of the message returned on a screen. In GUI, the severity code would indicate which Icon should be associated with the message in a message box. The severity code is not to be used for program logic. Program logic should be on the exception which is indicated by the return code

TATTRUSR.NAME: ROLLBACK_INDICATOR
TATTRUSR.DESC: Description: A flag requesting that the operation invoker rollback changes made to persistent storage.

TATTRUSR.NAME: ORIGIN_SERVID
TATTRUSR.DESC: Description: A unique number which identifies an installed copy of a component executable. Note: Some organizations may prefer to keep the value of the origin server identifier less than 2 to the power of 32 so the value can be transferred to or from widely-used 32-bit numeric fields.

TATTRUSR.NAME: CONTEXT_STRING
TATTRUSR.DESC:
Full Name: Exception Context String
Description: This string can be returned by a component and used to contain additional information about the context of the exception. It is not a message explaining the exception, but instead can contain data that could be put into a formatted message by one of the exception message services. It should use a forward slash (\) character to separate data. This standard allows the message services to determine what data is available. If parameter based messages are to be used, it is the responsibility of the component raising the exception to format a valid Context_String, even if its only placing empty forward slashes. If a forward slash is required in the context data string, surround the string segment in double quotations to isolate the string.

TATTRUSR.NAME: RETURN_CODE
TATTRUSR.DESC: Description: Return code is used to return a standardized code that indicates the type of failure or exception encountered during the operation execution. Note: Refer to CBD standards for a list of standardized return codes.

TATTRUSR.NAME: REASON_CODE
TATTRUSR.DESC: Description: Reason code is used to provide a reason why the failure or exception occurred. Reason code values may be defined in the specification. If so, the user of the operation can code to such values. Additional unspecified reason codes may be exported. These may vary by implementation, so component suppliers can provide explanations specific to their implementations.

TATTRUSR.NAME: SEND_COMMAND
TATTRUSR.DESC: Yapýlmasý istenen iþlemin kodu. Bu komponenti kullanan yordam bu alaný kullanarak yapýlmasý istediði iþlemi belirtir.

TATTRUSR.NAME: CLIENT_COMMAND

TATTRUSR.NAME: COMPONENT_CD
TATTRUSR.DESC: This is the 3 character code which uniquely defines a specification. It will be used to facilitate loading and unloading of all exception messages for a particular specification.

TATTRUSR.NAME: IMPLEMENTATION_ID
TATTRUSR.DESC: A unique number which identifies an Implementation of a Component Specification. Note: Some organizations may prefer to keep the value of this identifier less than 2 to the power of 32 so the value can be transferred to or from widely-used 32-bit numeric fields.

TATTRUSR.NAME: SPECIFICATION_ID
TATTRUSR.DESC:
A unique number which identifies a specification for a component.
NOTE: Some organizations may prefer to keep the value of this identifier to less than 2 to the power of 32 so the value can be transferred to or from widely-used 32-bit numeric fields.

TATTRUSR.NAME: DIALECT_CD
TATTRUSR.DESC:
Full Name: Dialect Code
Description: This attribute is used to define a dialect code. The dialect code is a code defining a particular dialect or language that pertains to the type of data that can be handled within a component. A dialect code is used to define the the manner in which textual information should be stored or presented.

TATTRUSR.NAME: ACTIVITY_CD
TATTRUSR.DESC:
Full Name: Exception Activity Code
Description: A code value allowing services to accept in, or return out an action indicator. This would be similar to the COMMAND value maintained by Composer, and would usually be used in a Case structure to perform multiple actions. It also can be used to return some context information about an exception that was being raised.

TATTRUSR.NAME: MESSAGE_TX
TATTRUSR.DESC:
Full Name: Exception Message Text
Description: This string returns the message (via other component exception messaging services) to the application for use. It is also used internal to the component if the application has requested that the component display a message. Note, if the message is to be used by Composer as an exit state message, it can only support 80 characters of data.

TATTRUSR.NAME: MESSAGE_NAME_TX
TATTRUSR.DESC:
Full Name: Exception Message Name
Description: This is the name of the Exception Message and is used during the maintenance of Exception Messages as a mechanism to locate particular exception conditions or exception message text.

TATTRUSR.NAME: ATTRIBUTE_NAME_TX
TATTRUSR.DESC:
Full Name: Attribute Name
Description: This attribute is used to define an attribute value for Hilight fields on a transaction screen. This field will indicate the name of the field to highlight on the screen. The field name will typically be the same name as the public field name found in the public data of a component called from the transaction.

TATTRUSR.NAME: ORIGIN_SERV_TX
TATTRUSR.DESC: This attribute is used to provide a description of the ORIGIN_SERVID.

TATTRUSR.NAME: SPECIFICATION_STRING_TX
TATTRUSR.DESC: A description of the specification for a component.

TATTRUSR.NAME: IMPLEMENTATION_STRING_TX
TATTRUSR.DESC:
Description: This attribute is used to provide a description of the implementation of a component as defined by the Implementation Id.
Example: Executable Id Executable String 1474849494 Party Enterprise Object built using Composer 3 OS2/C

TATTRUSR.NAME: CHECKSUM
TATTRUSR.DESC:
Full Name: Exception Checksum
Description: This string represents a 32 bit checksum, calculated on a data block. It is used to ensure that data over or under runs have not occurred. It is expected that a set of external action blocks, provided by Castek, can be used to calculate a checksum.
